author: TAMAGHNA BANERJEE AND MONOTOSH CHAKRABORTY
description: A psychologist's rape allegation against a student at a Kolkata management institute faces hurdles as the complainant and her family refuse to cooperate with the investigation. Despite forensic evidence collection and police efforts to gather information, the family's silence and a lack of engagement with authorities are impeding the probe.
title: Kolkata B-school rape probe hits wall as 'survivor', her advocate father won't speak

author: MANOJ CHAURASIA
description: Patna residents are anxious as booth-level officers (BLOs) haven't collected enumeration forms (EFs) before the July 25 deadline. Despite Election Commission claims of 80% collection, many like Raju Sinha and Munna Singh are still waiting.
title: Residents of Patna await booth-level-officers as deadline for enumeration forms nears

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Aamir Khan and Genelia Deshmukh's film 'Sitaare Zameen Par' is a big hit. The sports drama earned Rs 3 crore on Sunday. Its domestic collection is now Rs 160.75 crore. The film stars neurodivergent actors. It is about a basketball coach training players with disabilities. The film faces competition from new releases like 'Metro..In Dino' and 'Superman'.
title: ‘Sitaare Zameen Par’ BO collection day 24: Film crosses Rs 160 cr mark

author: TNN
description: China's embassy in Delhi voiced strong objections to recent remarks from Indian figures regarding Tibet and the Dalai Lama's reincarnation. The spokesperson emphasized India's commitment to recognizing Tibet as part of China and preventing anti-China political activities by Tibetans in India.
title: Tibet issue a thorn in ties with India, says Chinese envoy

author: AMBIKA PANDIT
description: Marking his 90th birthday, the Dalai Lama expressed gratitude to India for its hospitality since 1959, indirectly addressing China's claim over Tibet. He highlighted India's role as the land of Buddha and its support in preserving Tibetan culture and education. A declaration at the conference lauded his stance on his reincarnation and spiritual integrity.
title: We Tibetans deeply indebted to India for warm hospitality: Dalai Lama

author: DURGESH NANDAN JHA
description: Dr Abhijat Sheth has been appointed as the new chairperson of the National Medical Commission (NMC), succeeding Dr. B N Gangadhar, who stepped down due to health reasons. Dr. Sheth previously served as president of the National Board of Examination in Medical Sciences, which conducts NEET-PG exams.
title: Amid assessment reports 'scam', medical regulator gets a new chief

author: DIWAKAR
description: Prime Minister Modi nominated C Sadanandan Master, a victim of brutal political violence, to the Rajya Sabha. Sadanandan, whose legs were hacked off by CPM workers in 1994 for his RSS affiliation, exemplifies resilience. Despite the attack, he continued to advocate against violence and promote Hindutva.
title: From having legs hacked off to getting Rajya Sabha foothold: A Master's journey of grit

author: TNN
description: Bangladesh continues its "mango diplomacy" by sending 1,000 kg of Haribhanga mangoes to PM Narendra Modi, a gesture of goodwill amidst recent political shifts. This tradition, initiated by former PM Sheikh Hasina, aims to strengthen ties between Dhaka and New Delhi.
title: Ties bitter, but Bangladesh mango diplomacy still sweet enough
